title: Aerial survey shows sinkholes, muddy messes left by SoCal storm
text:
EMBED </> More News Videos <iframe width="476" height="267" src="http://abc7.com/video/embed/?pid=1761826" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> 
From massive sinkholes to muddy messes, AIR7 HD has been touring around Southern California to survey the damage left by the massive storm that pummeled the region on Friday. (KABC) KABC Saturday, February 18, 2017 07:12PM LOS ANGELES (KABC) -- AIR7 HD has been touring around Southern California to survey the damage left by the massive storm that pummeled the region on Friday.Downed trees, sinkholes that swallowed cars and trees, washed-out roads, muddy messes - that was the scene throughout SoCal.For a look at the survey of Southern California from the air, watch the video above.
